<br>
I will agree that my point is rather small and I only responded to your post because I thought it well put.  Think about this though, Xev is a first in force server and strongly opposed to raid schedules.  &quot;the comminuty&quot; of the time had many public discussions on it.  Now there is a VT rotation.  I am sure that every guild to follow the few people who made this agreement will be expected to do the same.<br>
<br>
The sleeper event remained because people feared the reprisal even though it outlived its original purpose which was nothing more than to preserve primal drops for everyone.  The VT rotation will stand also for every guild to follow.  Why?  It most likely preserves the sanity of xev guilds capabale of VT and that is good in a way.  This is a very large break of the xev traditions set by harm/av and it will effect everyone on the server who becomes VT capable.<br>
